  "instructions": {
    "L": [
      {
        "S": "Combine 8 oz ground beef, 8 oz ground pork, 1/3 cup breadcrumbs, 1/4 cup Parmesan, 2 tablespoons parsley, 3/4 teaspoon oregano, 3/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in a large bowl. Add 1 large egg and mix gently with your hands until just combined. Do not overwork the mixture or the meatballs will be dense. Shape into small meatballs, about 3/4 to 1 inch in diameter, to yield 40 to 50 meatballs. Transfer to a plate or baking sheet."
      },
      {
        "S": "Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Working in two batches to avoid crowding, add the meatballs and cook until golden brown on 2 to 3 sides, about 3 to 4 minutes per batch. The meatballs do not need to be cooked through as they will finish cooking in the broth. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate and set aside."
      },
      {
        "S": "Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large soup pot or Dutch oven over medium heat while the meatballs are browning. Add the 1 diced onion, 3 diced carrots, and 3 diced celery stalks. Saute for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the onion is soft and translucent and the carrots have begun to soften. Add the 4 cloves of minced garlic and 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning and saute for 1 minute more until fragrant."
      },
      {
        "S": "Pour in the 8 cups of chicken broth and the Parmesan rind if using. Increase heat to medium-high and bring to a boil. Add the browned meatballs and 3/4 cup pasta once boiling. Stir gently to prevent the pasta from sticking. Return to a boil, then reduce heat to medium-low."
      },
      {
        "S": "Cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the pasta is al dente and the meatballs are cooked through to an internal temperature of 165 degrees F."
      },
      {
        "S": "Remove the Parmesan rind if used. Stir in the 5 oz of baby spinach and cook until just wilted, about 1 minute. Taste the broth and adjust salt and pepper as needed."
      },
      {
        "S": "Ladle into bowls and top each serving generously with freshly grated Parmesan cheese and fresh cracked pepper. Serve with crusty bread."
      }
    ]
  },
  "notes": {
    "L": [
      {
        "S": "Gluten-Free Substitution: Use gluten-free breadcrumbs for the meatballs and substitute gluten-free small pasta such as rice-based ditalini or orzo to make this recipe gluten-free."
      },
      {
        "S": "Greens Variation: Escarole, endive, or kale are traditional alternatives to spinach. If using heartier greens, add them 5 minutes before the end of cooking rather than at the very end."
      },
      {
        "S": "Make-Ahead Tip: For meal prep or if planning leftovers, cook the pasta separately and add to individual bowls at serving time. This prevents the pasta from bloating and absorbing all the broth."
      },
      {
        "S": "Broth Tip: Homemade chicken stock makes a significant difference. If using store-bought, choose low-sodium to control seasoning. Simmering a Parmesan rind in the broth adds wonderful umami depth."
      },
      {
        "S": "Storage: Refrigerate in an airtight container for up to 3 days or freeze for up to 3 months. Pasta will continue to absorb broth as it sits so add extra broth when reheating."
      },
      {
        "S": "Food Safety: Ensure meatballs reach an internal temperature of 165 degrees F. When browning, meatballs are only seared on the outside and they finish cooking in the simmering broth."
      }
    ]
  },
